Johannesburg metro police recovered a hijacked truck with jamming devices and R50 million worth of smart televisions. This was announced by the City of Johannesburg&#8217;s MMC for Public Safety Michael Sun on Saturday morning. Sun also said two suspects were arrested and detained at the Johannesburg Central police station. Sun took to Twitter to share the news and photographs: Breaking- JMPD recovers hijacked truck, jamming devices&amp; R50 mil worth of Smart TV. 2 suspects arrested &amp; detained at SAPS Jhb Central pic.twitter.com/VJuNQqemuA &mdash; Michael Sun (@MichaelSun168) June 24, 2017 For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.